cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use VulnSieve in your research, please cite both the software and the paper below."

title: "VulnSieve CVE Program"
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-06-15"
url: "https://github.com/Kwabena-d/Vulnsieve"
license: MIT

authors:
  - family-names: Darko
    given-names: Stephen Kwabena
    affiliation: Montclair State University
  - family-names: Varickamackal Asokkumar
    given-names: Ramsagar
    affiliation: Montclair State University

abstract: >
  VulnSieve is a command-line tool that fetches CVE records from the NVD and
  compresses them from 300–800 words to ~50 tokens using the Anthropic Claude API,
  while extracting structured exploit schemas. Designed for use in multi-agent
  penetration testing pipelines where token efficiency and CVE recall reliability
  are critical.

keywords:
  - cybersecurity
  - CVE
  - NVD
  - LLM
  - penetration testing
  - LangChain
  - vulnerability analysis
  - multi-agent

references:
  - type: conference-paper
    title: "VulnSieve: LLM-Augmented CVE Compression for Autonomous Penetration Testing Pipelines"
